<p>Here at Tutora, our Birmingham tutors are ready to help! Whether you are seeking a Maths Tutor, English Tutor or Science Tutor, we have the right person for you. We cover the whole of Birmingham, so just enter your postcode and subject to find a private tutor and organise your home tuition. Remember, enter Primary, KS3, GCSE, A Level or Degree to narrow your search.</p>

<p>At Tutora, we also provide Language Tutors, so if you are seeking French, German or Spanish tuition, we’re happy to help.</p>



<h5>Grammar Schools, 11+ and Entrance Exams</h5>
<p>Birmingham has numerous grammar schools, many of which are part of the <a href="http://www.schoolsofkingedwardvi.co.uk/">King Edward system</a>, including <a href="http://www.camphillboys.bham.sch.uk/">Camp Hill Boys</a>, <a href="http://kechg.org.uk/">Camp Hill Girls</a>, <a href="http://web.keaston.bham.sch.uk">Aston</a>, <a href="http://www.kefw.org/">Five Ways</a>, <a href="http://www.kingedwardvi.bham.sch.uk">Handsworth</a> and the <a href="http://www.kes.org.uk">High School</a>. There is also <a href="http://www.bvgs.co.uk/">Bishop Vesey’s</a>, <a href="http://www.handsworth.bham.sch.uk">Handsworth</a> and <a href="http://www.suttcold.bham.sch.uk/scgsg/">Sutton Coldfield</a>. We have experienced 11 plus tutors who will be happy to help your child prepare for the entrance examinations.</p>

<h5>Universities</h5>
Birmingham has a very high student population. There are the <a href="http://www.birmingham.ac.uk/index.aspx">University of Birmingham</a>, <a href="http://www.bcu.ac.uk">Birmingham City University</a>, <a href="http://www.aston.ac.uk/">Aston University</a> and <a href="http://www.newman.ac.uk">Newman University</a>. We also have tutors who tutor to degree level, or help secure the A Level grades your child needs to gain their university place.
